description: MEMORANDUM Opinion and Order: For the reasons stated in the attached Memorandum Opinion and Order, having reconsidered the prior attorneys' fee award in light of the Seventh Circuit's instructions and the additional examples of awards provided by Co-Counsel, the Court grants Co-Counsel's renewed motion for attorneys' fees 6910 but decreases the award to $51,660,000.00, which is 30% of the settlement fund after deducting the expenses and incentive awards. Andren also sought discovery from experts the Court cited in the prior order to the extent the Court continued to rely on those opinions, and in the alternative moved to strike the opinions. Because this opinion and order is not based on those expert opinions, no discovery is warranted, and the motion to strike 6931 is denied as moot. Signed by the Honorable Thomas M. Durkin on 7/3/2024. Mailed notice. (ecw, ) (Entered: 07/03/2024)
